called?
TheFacebook.[5]
When did TheFacebook become
Facebook?
The corporate name changed to Facebook, Inc. on May 11, 2005;
the service publicly dropped "The" after the purchase of
facebook.com in August 2005.[3][5][6]
Is Facebook now called Meta?
The parent company is Meta Platforms, Inc.; the social network is
still Facebook.[1][4]
